fixes #1331

issue.title: Windows: add miller to winget
issue.body:
since a while Microsoft has [a package manager for windows: winget](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/package-manager/) and it's possible to add software software to their repository ([documentation](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/package-manager/package/repository), [repo](https://github.com/microsoft/winget-pkgs)).

it'd be great if miller could be added there, so that it can be installed on any windows 10 & 11 system using `winget install miller`. this would lower the barrier for a windows installation (and the ability to keep it up to date) significantly (not everyone has choco installed and now that winget exists i don't see the point in using a 3rd party tool anymore which i'd first have to install).

alternatively you could also package it in the MS Store as winget can also install packages from there.

commits.message:
add `winget` to README (#1414)

@teo-tsirpanis added miller to `winget` with
microsoft/winget-pkgs#123507 (thanks!).
accordingly it should also be mentioned in the README so that people are
aware of it.

fixes #1331

v1.17.1

What's Changed

  • s2: Fix S2 "best" dictionary wrong encoding by @​klauspost in klauspost/compress#871

  • s2: Fix EstimateBlockSize on 6&7 length input by @​klauspost in klauspost/compress#867
  • tests: Fuzzing Coverage Expansion by @​viktoriia-lsg in klauspost/compress#866
  • tests: Set FSE decompress fuzzer max limit by @​klauspost in klauspost/compress#868
  • tests: Fuzzing Coverage Expansion (#2) by @​viktoriia-lsg in klauspost/compress#870

New Contributors

  • @​viktoriia-lsg made their first contribution in klauspost/compress#866
  • @​fakefloordiv made their first contribution in klauspost/compress#869

Full Changelog: https://github.com/klauspost/compress/compare/v1.17.0...v1.17.1

  • Add dictionary builder by @​klauspost in klauspost/compress#853
  • Add xerial snappy read/writer by @​klauspost in klauspost/compress#838
  • flate: Add limited window compression by @​klauspost in klauspost/compress#843
  • s2: Do 2 overlapping match checks by @​klauspost in klauspost/compress#839

  • tests: Fix OSS fuzzer t.Run by @​klauspost in klauspost/compress#852
